The paper deals with straightening out poly-line drawings, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the width and height of the resulting drawings, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions some applications of the result, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
